      "item": {
        "id": "2503657a-fd40-44f2-b112-4ce5ac2666c6",
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "In 1928, as part of a lecture reviewing \"The Early History of Radio in the United States\", H. P. Davis, commenting on entertainment offerings, asserted that \"Reginald Fessenden, probably the first to attempt this, broadcast a program Christmas Eve 1906\", but didn't provide any additional details, and his comment was little noticed at the time."
