      "text": "The first widely publicized information about Fessenden's early broadcasts did not appear until 1932, when an article prepared by former Fessenden associate Samuel M. Kintner, \"Pittsburgh's Contributions to Radio\", appeared in the December 1932 issue of ''The Proceedings of the Institute of Radio Engineers''. This reviewed information included in a January 29, 1932 letter sent by Fessenden to Kintner. (Fessenden subsequently died five months before Kintner's article appeared). "
